All statistical analyses were performed with R version 4.1.2 ( R
). Significant differences among three plant species were tested by one-way analyses of variance (ANOVA), using the multcomp package. The analysis employed the AUCEm as a dependent variable and the plant species as an independent variable. The ANOVA was followed by a Tukey–Kramer post-hoc analysis to test the pairwise comparisons. The unpaired t -test was used to test the significant difference between two plant species in the behavioral assay and colorimetry;
p <
0.05 was considered statistically significant. The boxplot in Fig. 2 was depicted using the ggplot2 package. For effect sizes, we computed the standardized mean difference expressed as Hedge’ s g using the compute.es package.
